@section General

This backend accepts SWEET16 instructions as defined by Steve Wozniak
and used in the Apple II computer ROM. An interpreter for this pseudo
CPU, with 16 16-bit registers, can also be ported to other 6502-based
systems.

The target address type is 16 bit.

Instructions consist of one, two (branches) or three bytes (@code{SET}
instruction) and require no alignment. Data requires no alignment either.

